    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>In the 60&#39;s &#038; 70&#39;s we were stationed in Germany 3 times and my favorite lunch (usually on the Appetizer menu) was Russian Eggs. The dish varied from gasthaus to gasthaus but usually consisted of a meat salad (chopped roast beef or ham, mayo) with 2 hardcooked eggs (halved and turned cut side down) on top, napped with a sauce (maybe mayo diluted with sour cream) and garnished with lox and caviar.  So delicious!</p>
    </div>

