  <li id="comment-24106" class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/01493708300940204826" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Molly</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2011/05/pile-it-on/#comment-24106"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2011-05-15T02:30:29-04:00">Sunday, May 15, 2011 at 2:30 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Hi, all!</p>
<p>To answer a few questions:</p>
<p>Caroline, if you&#39;ve got a mushroom-hater on your hands, I&#39;m thinking you might want to skip this recipe entirely.  It&#39;s really all about the mushrooms.  (And the onions and eggs, too, of course. But there are lots and lots of mushrooms in there.)</p>
<p>Anonymous, you&#39;re right, re: Best Foods!   I grew up with it as Hellmann&#39;s, so I somehow still think of it by that name, even though the label says Best Foods.  Apologies for the confusion.</p>
<p>Alexia, sadly, I think Matthew still wouldn&#39;t touch it.</p>
<p>Hortus2, my first inclination is to tell you to just leave the mustard out.  I&#39;ll bet it would still be delicious.  But if you notice that the flavor is missing something, hot sauce might perk it up&#8230;</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
